description: Returns the object types for a specific domain.

parameters.name: DomainName
parameters.description: The unique name of the domain.

parameters.name: ObjectTypeName
parameters.description: The name of the profile object type.

nested_items.name: ObjectTypeName
nested_items.description: The name of the profile object type.

nested_items.name: Description
nested_items.description: The description of the profile object type.

nested_items.name: TemplateId
nested_items.description: A unique identifier for the object template.

nested_items.name: ExpirationDays
nested_items.description: The number of days until the data in the object expires.

nested_items.name: EncryptionKey
nested_items.description: The customer-provided key to encrypt the profile object that will be created in this profile object type.

nested_items.name: AllowProfileCreation
nested_items.description: Indicates whether a profile should be created when data is received if one doesn't exist for an object of this type. The default is FALSE. If the AllowProfileCreation flag is set to FALSE, then the service tries to fetch a standard profile and associate this object with the profile. If it is set to TRUE, and if no match is found, then the service creates a new standard profile.

nested_items.name: SourceLastUpdatedTimestampFormat
nested_items.description: The format of your sourceLastUpdatedTimestamp that was previously set up.

nested_items.name: MaxAvailableProfileObjectCount
nested_items.description: The amount of provisioned profile object max count available.

nested_items.name: MaxProfileObjectCount
nested_items.description: The amount of profile object max count assigned to the object type.

nested_items.name: Source
nested_items.description: (string) ---

nested_items.name: Source
nested_items.description: A field of a ProfileObject. For example: _source.FirstName, where '_source' is a ProfileObjectType of a Zendesk user and 'FirstName' is a field in that ObjectType.

nested_items.name: Target
nested_items.description: The location of the data in the standard ProfileObject model. For example: _profile.Address.PostalCode.

nested_items.name: ContentType
nested_items.description: The content type of the field. Used for determining equality when searching.

nested_items.name: StandardIdentifiers
nested_items.description: (string) ---

nested_items.name: StandardIdentifiers
nested_items.description: (list) ---

nested_items.name: StandardIdentifiers
nested_items.description: The types of keys that a ProfileObject can have. Each ProfileObject can have only 1 UNIQUE key but multiple PROFILE keys. PROFILE, ASSET, CASE, or ORDER means that this key can be used to tie an object to a PROFILE, ASSET, CASE, or ORDER respectively. UNIQUE means that it can be used to uniquely identify an object. If a key a is marked as SECONDARY, it will be used to search for profiles after all other PROFILE keys have been searched. A LOOKUP_ONLY key is only used to match a profile but is not persisted to be used for searching of the profile. A NEW_ONLY key is only used if the profile does not already exist before the object is ingested, otherwise it is only used for matching objects to profiles.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: FieldNames
nested_items.description: The reference for the key name of the fields map.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: CreatedAt
nested_items.description: The timestamp of when the domain was created.

nested_items.name: LastUpdatedAt
nested_items.description: The timestamp of when the domain was most recently edited.
